content: I wasn't born a demigod. I had human parents. They... They took one look and decided they did not want me. They threw me into the sea, like I was nothing. Somehow I was found by the gods. They gave me the hook. They made me, Maui. And back to the humans I went. I gave them islands, fire, coconuts. Anything they could ever want.
author: Ron Clements, John Musker
